					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">So you generate a table of these weights for each fractional position you will be using, then run through and apply them.</div><br />In the Super NES DSP, the Gaussian interpolation stage immediately after BRR decoding does pretty much exactly this. It has 256 sets of four weights, one for each 1/256 fractional position. (Half of those sets are reflected.) See &quot;4-Point Gaussian Interpolation&quot; in <a href="http://nocash.emubase.de/fullsnes.txt" class="postlink">fullsnes</a> for the details.</div>

